						               													<description>This is both a collectible vinyl miniatures series and physical manipulation wargame. Each player builds his army (Green or Blue) based on a points limits, with each figures' points value based on the unit's rarity and value to the game. Each players' &amp;quot;Prized Possession&amp;quot; is placed on the gaming area, this represents the enemy's objective in the battle, traditionally this is a bowl of Kale (for the Blue player) and a bowl of Cheeseballs (for the Green player). Players then take turns placing their figures, with no figure being more than 2&amp;quot; forward of the protected objective. Obstacles are then placed and the game can begin. Each player has a total of for actions per turn, with the first player taking all 4 actions, then the 2nd player goes. Actions consist of Marching and Shooting. To March the player places a move token next to the figure intended to move and flicks the token forward, after that the figure is moved up to the token. Shooting is similar, the Shoot token is placed and flicked toward the intended enemy target. Figures are captured or wounded based on these their characteristics and the characteristics of the shooing figure. Many of the rarer figures in this game have special skills and rules. Some of the figures are: Generals, Tankers, Flyers, Snipers, Privates and Paratroopers. The physical manipulation mechanism is reminiscent of Subbuteo.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
